  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nFollowing up on https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/3232\r\n\r\nI ultimately want to be able to test that a contract call will fail when trying to write a contract > code size under [EIP-170](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-170.md).\r\n\r\nNot sure if this is best done with config (CLI flag or `foundry.toml`) vs. a forge-std/Vm function but I could see use cases for both (especially the latter where you want to be permissive for large test suites but fail particular tests).\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
